# ESLint Plugins

Plugins extend ESLint with rules, processors, and configs for specific ecosystems. In flat config, plugins are imported as JavaScript objects — not referenced as strings.

## Plugin Configuration in Flat Config

```javascript
import example from "eslint-plugin-example";

export default [
  {
    plugins: {
      example,              // Registers the plugin under namespace "example"
    },
    rules: {
      "example/rule-1": "error",   // Use namespace/rule-name format
      "example/rule-2": "warn",
    },
  },
];
```

The `plugins` object maps namespaces to plugin objects. Rule names use `namespace/rule-name` format.

## typescript-eslint

The most important ESLint plugin — adds TypeScript-specific rules and type-aware linting.

```bash
npm install --save-dev typescript-eslint
```

```javascript
// eslint.config.mjs
import js from "@eslint/js";
import tseslint from "typescript-eslint";

export default tseslint.config(
  js.configs.recommended,
  ...tseslint.configs.recommended,              // Basic TS rules
  // ...tseslint.configs.recommendedTypeChecked, // Type-aware rules (slower)
  // ...tseslint.configs.strict,                 // Stricter rules
  // ...tseslint.configs.strictTypeChecked,      // Strict + type-aware
  {
    languageOptions: {
      parserOptions: {
        projectService: true,                     // Enable type-aware linting
        tsconfigRootDir: import.meta.dirname,
      },
    },
  },
);
```

**Key rules:**
| Rule | Purpose |
|------|----------|
| `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` | TS-aware unused vars (replaces base rule) |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` | Warns on `any` usage |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-floating-promises` | Requires handling promises (type-aware) |
| `@typescript-eslint/await-thenable` | Prevents awaiting non-thenables (type-aware) |
| `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` | Enforces `import type` syntax |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-unsafe-assignment` | Prevents `any` propagation (type-aware) |

## eslint-plugin-react

Rules for React components and JSX.

```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-plugin-react eslint-plugin-react-hooks
```

```javascript
import react from "eslint-plugin-react";
import reactHooks from "eslint-plugin-react-hooks";

export default [
  {
    files: ["**/*.{jsx,tsx}"],
    plugins: { react, "react-hooks": reactHooks },
    languageOptions: {
      parserOptions: { ecmaFeatures: { jsx: true } },
    },
    rules: {
      ...reactHooks.configs.recommended.rules,
      "react/react-in-jsx-scope": "off",     // Not needed in React 17+
      "react/prop-types": "off",              // Not needed with TypeScript
      "react-hooks/exhaustive-deps": "warn",
    },
    settings: { react: { version: "detect" } },
  },
];
```

## eslint-plugin-import

Rules for import/export syntax, module resolution, and import ordering.

```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-plugin-import
```

```javascript
import importPlugin from "eslint-plugin-import";

export default [
  {
    plugins: { import: importPlugin },
    rules: {
      "import/order": ["error", {
        groups: ["builtin", "external", "internal", "parent", "sibling", "index"],
        "newlines-between": "always",
        alphabetize: { order: "asc" },
      }],
      "import/no-duplicates": "error",
      "import/no-unresolved": "error",
      "import/no-cycle": "warn",
    },
    settings: {
      "import/resolver": {
        node: true,
        typescript: true,  // needs eslint-import-resolver-typescript
      },
    },
  },
];
```

## eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y

Accessibility rules for JSX elements.

```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y
```

```javascript
import jsxA11y from "eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y";

export default [
  {
    files: ["**/*.{jsx,tsx}"],
    plugins: { "jsx-a11y": jsxA11y },
    rules: {
      ...jsxA11y.configs.recommended.rules,
    },
  },
];
```

## ESLint + Prettier

Use `eslint-config-prettier` to disable formatting rules that conflict with Prettier:

```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-config-prettier
```

```javascript
import prettier from "eslint-config-prettier";

export default [
  js.configs.recommended,
  prettier,  // Must be last to override formatting rules
];
```

Note: `eslint-plugin-prettier` (running Prettier as an ESLint rule) is discouraged — run Prettier separately.

## Local Plugins (Custom Rules)

Create a rule file and register it as a local plugin:

```javascript
// rules/no-foo.js
export default {
  meta: {
    type: "problem",
    docs: { description: "Disallow use of foo()" },
    fixable: "code",
    schema: [],
  },
  create(context) {
    return {
      CallExpression(node) {
        if (node.callee.name === "foo") {
          context.report({
            node,
            message: "Do not use foo()",
            fix(fixer) {
              return fixer.replaceText(node, "bar()");
            },
          });
        }
      },
    };
  },
};
```

```javascript
// eslint.config.mjs
import noFoo from "./rules/no-foo.js";

export default [
  {
    plugins: {
      local: { rules: { "no-foo": noFoo } },
    },
    rules: {
      "local/no-foo": "error",
    },
  },
];
```

## Popular Plugin Reference

| Plugin | Purpose | Install |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `typescript-eslint` | TypeScript rules and parser | `npm i -D typescript-eslint` |
| `eslint-plugin-react` | React component rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-react` |
| `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` | React hooks rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-react-hooks` |
| `eslint-plugin-import` | Import/export rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-import` |
| `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` | Accessibility rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` |
| `eslint-plugin-jest` | Jest test rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-jest` |
| `eslint-plugin-vitest` | Vitest test rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-vitest` |
| `eslint-plugin-n` | Node.js rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-n` |
| `eslint-plugin-unicorn` | Various useful rules | `npm i -D eslint-plugin-unicorn` |
| `eslint-config-prettier` | Disable formatting rules | `npm i -D eslint-config-prettier` |
| `@next/eslint-plugin-next` | Next.js rules | `npm i -D @next/eslint-plugin-next` |
